â¡ï¸ go to @audidriven stories section
.
I type this 1st log entry from Barcelona - ~ 2.000 Km into our 8.000 #iberitron road trip
.
Short summary how things went down till now:
* Austria is HPC heaven - except in Villach (see the drama in @audidriven story iberitron 02)
* Italy is getting better - although after our 3rd visit to @ionity.official Portogruaro - this location is definitely a dump (stinking trash containers next to the chargers, littering, not appealing at all
* @ionity.official France has a serious problem (1st station 4 stalls: 1 of 4 working = 1 broken - where I parked 1st, 2nd working - where I reparked, 3&4 only charging with ~35kW / 2nd station 6 stalls: 2 out of six delivered the full speed (150kW for the e-tron), the other ~35kW. Again lucky as I got the 2nd working one after reparking) Got lucky
* Spain ğŸ‡ªğŸ‡¸ - a little to early to tell but was already pleasantly surprised, as proven by this picture. In the middle of nowhere - Figueres - I found this working (!) HPC charger. Biggest challenge was to get the operator app working as it does not accept any of the charging cards
* A general not surprising rule: try to always charge before the night (like in this case) or even better over night as currently in our Barcelona hotel. For me the charging stops are part of the adventure (now locations, new experiences) but apparently my family thinks differently ğŸ˜‚. Yesterday we had zero charging stops (â€œboringâ€ for me, enjoyable for family)
.
When we arrive at my moms place near Malaga I will try to do a more detailed day by day posts if desired ğŸ˜‰
.
